This paper is about building machine learning models and analyzing neural networks, which falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on generating distribution-conforming examples to understand model behavior, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. The method also involves probing for ambivalent predictions and adversarial examples, which are common topics in neural networks (cs.NE) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
